This topic explains how to install <%= vars.platform_name %> on Microsoft Azure using Terraform.

To install <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> on Azure using Terraform, do the following:

1. Deploy Pivotal Operations Manager. See [Deploying Ops Manager on Azure Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/azure/prepare-env-terraform.html).

1. Configure BOSH Director. See [Configuring BOSH Director on Azure Using Terraform](/platform/ops-manager/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/azure/config-terraform.html).

1. Configure <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>. See [Configuring <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %>](https://docs.pivotal.io/application-service/<%= vars.current_major_version.sub('.', '-') %>/operating/configure-pas.html).
